## Limitations

The findings are based on available literature and studies, which may not cover all aspects of rehabilitation programs globally. The effectiveness of rehabilitation can vary depending on the specific program, the population it serves, and the context in which it is implemented. Additionally, some studies may have methodological limitations that could affect the generalizability of their results. Further research is needed to explore the long-term impacts of rehabilitation on crime reduction across different settings.